  "source": {
    "plain_text": "K-means Clustering: Partitional clustering. Each cluster is associated with a centroid. Each point is assigned to the cluster whose centroid is the closest. Number of clusters, k, must be specified. Algorithm: 1. Select k points as initial centroids. 2. Repeat: Form k clusters by assigning all points to their closest centroids. Recompute the centroid of each cluster. Until centroids don't change.",
